Stephen Walker has provided the following statement and has also provided t=
he attached qualifications and capability statements for your reference:



Hi Grant,



Please see attached as requested.  I have also included copy of our legisla=
tive and regulatory capability statement.



Note that this building is within the scope limitations of the Standard NZS=
 3604:2011.  NZS 3604:2011 is a cited means of compliance with building cod=
e clause B1 =E2=80=93 Structure for timber framed buildings not requiring s=
pecific engineering design.  This means that there is no legislative requir=
ement for engaging a structural engineer for design requirements for the re=
pair of this building.  As such, any repair or construction carried out in =
accordance with the Standard is deemed to satisfy the relevant provisions o=
f the building code and the Building Act 2004.



Further, considering the knowledge and experience provided by ASURNZ person=
nel regarding the assessment of fire damaged timber framed buildings, inclu=
ding my knowledge and experience, I doubt there would be any additional ben=
efit gained by engaging a structural engineer for this claim.  However, sho=
uld any design requirements that sit outside the scope limitations of NZS 3=
604:2011 and that require specific engineering design become apparent durin=
g scoping of repairs, I confirm that we will in that instance seek engineer=
ing design from a suitably experienced Chartered Professional Engineer (CPE=
ng).



Kind regards,



Stephen Walker

Principal Consultant



